        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 2:13PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 213 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 40
miles southwest of Battle Mountain, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rainfall along with gusty winds could knock down tree
limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage
to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Lander
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
